    "Body": " Content Writer AXEL - Las Vegas, NV Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $43,000 - $61,000 a year Qualifications Content Creation Technical Writing Marketing Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description AXEL is looking for a dynamic content writer in Las Vegas, NV. This person will be: A great writer \u2013 Your words dance, your sentences sing, your writing is fresh, eloquent, and endlessly informative, swaying, and entertaining. A thinker \u2013 Each staff writer will be a thinker and a star in his or her own right. You\u2019ll be smart enough to grasp complicated issues and explain them simply enough for any reasonably intelligent person to understand. A self-starter \u2013 You must be able to work with minimal supervision. Our executive team will guide you, and will sometimes assign you stories or content to write, but for the most part you\u2019ll take the initiative to come up with, enhance and update the current focus, and pursue unique ideas yourself. A hard worker \u2013 We have a lot to prove and we can\u2019t afford to take it easy. Independent \u2013 Good writers operate without fear or favor. You\u2019ll be ok with pursuing a spectrum of rejections in the service of finding the most meaningful truth and facts, and with being part of a company that does the same. Versatile \u2013 There\u2019s nothing more boring than a writer who writes about the same thing all the time. We want our writer to get out of their comfort zone and learn new things. If you need to become knowledgeable on something within a week and you know nothing about it, you\u2019ll relish the challenge. Responsibilities: Responsible for providing advanced creative advice and writing support for the development and implementation of moderately complex marketing communication materials. Consults with business leaders to identify business objectives. Evaluates the effectiveness of communication plans, strategies, copy and materials, and recommends solutions, communication strategies and implementation approaches. Collaborates with creative teams on customer business needs and develops and implements communication objectives solutions. Researches, writes, edits, and reviews content for traditionally printed programs (marketing collateral, trade publication advertising, direct mail, etc.) and digital programs (blog articles, online advertising, micro sites, landing pages, text campaigns, social media, etc.). Ensures all materials meet internal and external business and legal standards, and follows appropriate corporate and directorate standards, guidelines, and approval processes. Identifies improvements/efficiencies that support operational excellence, and supports business initiatives (plain language, standardization, going paperless, etc.). Requirements: Must have BA/BS degree; preferably in Marketing, English, Communications, or related field. 3-5 years of related experience; or any combination of education and experience, which would provide an equivalent background. Experience in technology, blockchain, and/or technical writing a plus. Additional Information: Only applicants that have provided salary expectations will be considered Unfortunately, we cannot consider foreign applicants with practical training visas Job Type: Full-time Experience: Content Creation: 3 years (Preferred) Marketing: 3 years (Preferred) Education: Bachelor's (Preferred) Location: Las Vegas, NV (Required) Work authorization: United States (Required) Application Question: What are your salary expectations for this role? Schedule: Monday to Friday Company's website: https://axel.network/ Company's Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/pg/AxelUnlimited/about/ "
